 39769                                  ;	Modification history:
 39770                                  ;
 39771                                  ;		Created: ARR 30 March 1983
 39772                                  ;		AN000	version 4.0 jan. 1988
 39773                                  ;		A007	PTM 3957 - fake vesrion for IBMCACHE.COM
 39774                                  ;		A008	PTM 4070 - fake version for MS WINDOWS
 39775                                  ;
 39776                                  ;		M000	added support for loading programs into UMBs 7/9/90
 39777                                  ;
 39778                                  ;		M004 - MS PASCAL 3.2 support. Please see under tag M003 in 
 39779                                  ;		       dossym.inc. 7/30/90
 39780                                  ;		M005 - Support for EXE programs with out STACK segment and 
 39781                                  ;		       with resident size < 64K - 256 bytes. A 256 byte 
 39782                                  ;		       stack is provided at the end of the program. Note that
 39783                                  ;		       only SP is changed.
 39784                                  ;		M020 - Fix for Rational bug for details see exepatch.asm
 39785                                  ;
 39786                                  ;		M028 - 4b04 implementation
 39787                                  ;
 39788                                  ;		M029 - Support for EXEs without stack rewritten. If EXE is
 39789                                  ;			in memory block >= 64K, sp = 0. If memory block
 39790                                  ;			obtained is <64K, point sp at the end of the memory
 39791                                  ;			block. For EXEs smaller than 64K, 256 bytes are still
 39792                                  ;			added for a stack segment which may be needed if it
 39793                                  ;			is loaded in low memory situations.
 39794                                  ;
 39795                                  ;		M030 - Fixing bug in EXEPACPATCH & changing 4b04 to 4b05
 39796                                  ;
 39797                                  ;		M040 - Bug #3052. The environment sizing code would flag a
 39798                                  ;			a bad environment if it reached 32767 bytes. Changed
 39799                                  ;			to allow 32768 bytes of environment.
 39800                                  ;
 39801                                  ;		M047 - Release the allocated UMB when we failed to load a 
 39802                                  ;		       COM file high. Also ensure that if the biggest block
 39803                                  ;		       into which we load the com file is less than 64K then
 39804                                  ;		       we provide atleast 256 bytes of stack to the user.
 39805                                  ;
 39806                                  ;		M050 - Made Lie table search CASE insensitive
 39807                                  ;
 39808                                  ;		M060 - Removed special version table from the kernal and
 39809                                  ;                      put it in a device drive which puts the address
 39810                                  ;                      in the DOS DATA area location UU_IFS_DOS_CALL
 39811                                  ;		       as a DWORD.
 39812                                  ;
 39813                                  ;		M063 - Modified UMB support. If the HIGH_ONLY bit is set on
 39814                                  ;		       entry do not try to load low if there is no space in
 39815                                  ;		       UMBs.
 39816                                  ;
 39817                                  ;		M068 - Support for copy protect apps. Call ChkCopyProt to 
 39818                                  ;		       set a20off_count. Set bit EXECA20BIT in DOS_FLAG. Also
 39819                                  ;		       change return address to LeaveDos if AL=5.
 39820                                  ;
 39821                                  ;               20-Jul-1992 bens  Added ifdef RESTRICTED_BUILD code that
 39822                                  ;                      controls building a version of MSDOS.SYS that only
 39823                                  ;                      runs programs from a fixed list (defined in the
 39824                                  ;                      file RESTRICT.INC).  Search for "RESTRICTED_BUILD"
 39825                                  ;                      for details.  This feature is used to build a
 39826                                  ;                      "special" version of DOS that can be handed out to
 39827                                  ;                      OEM/ISV customers as part of a "service" disk.
