 43609                                  ;**	SFNFree - Allocate a Free SFN/SFT
 43610                                  ;----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 43611                                  ;	SFNFree scans through the sf table looking for a free entry
 43612                                  ;	If it finds one it partially allocates it by setting SFT_REF_COUNT = -1
 43613                                  ;
 43614                                  ;	The problem is that we want to mark the SFT busy so that other threads
 43615                                  ;	can't allocate the SFT before we're finished marking it up.  However,
 43616                                  ;	we can't just mark it busy because we may get blown out of our open
 43617                                  ;	by INT24 and leave the thing orphaned.	To solve this we mark it
 43618                                  ;	"allocation in progress" by setting SFT_REF_COUNT = -1.  If we see
 43619                                  ;	an SFT with this value we look to see if it belongs to this user
 43620                                  ;	and process.  If it does belong to us then it must be an orphan
 43621                                  ;	and we reclaim it.
 43622                                  ;
 43623                                  ;	BUGBUG - improve the performance. I guess it's smaller to call SFFromSFN
 43624                                  ;		over and over, but we could at least set a high water mark...
 43625                                  ;		cause an N^2 loop calling slow SFFromSFN is real slow, too slow
 43626                                  ;		even though this is not a frequently called routine - jgl
 43627                                  ;
 43628                                  ;	ENTRY	(ss) = DOSDATA
 43629                                  ;	EXIT	'C' clear if no error
 43630                                  ;		  (bx) = SFN
 43631                                  ;		  (es:di) = pointer to SFT
 43632                                  ;		  es:[di].SFT_REF_COUNT = -1
 43633                                  ;		'C' set if error
 43634                                  ;		  (al) = error code
