 44872                                  ;Break	<CheckOwner - verify ownership of handles from server>
 44873                                  ;----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 44874                                  ;   CheckOwner - Due to the ability of the server to close file handles for a
 44875                                  ;   process without the process knowing it (delete/rename of open files, for
 44876                                  ;   example), it is possible for the redirector to issue a call to a handle
 44877                                  ;   that it soes not rightfully own. We check here to make sure that the
 44878                                  ;   issuing process is the owner of the SFT. At the same time, we do a
 44879                                  ;   SFFromHandle to really make sure that the SFT is good.
 44880                                  ;
