 44955                                  ;
 44956                                  ;	Created: MZ 4 April 1983
 44957                                  ;		 MZ 18 April 1983   Make TransFCB handle extended FCBs
 44958                                  ;		 AR 2 June 1983     Define/Delete macro for NET redir.
 44959                                  ;		 MZ 3 Nov 83	    Fix InitCDS to reset length to 2
 44960                                  ;		 MZ 4 Nov 83	    Fix NetAssign to use STRLEN only
 44961                                  ;		 MZ 18 Nov 83	    Rewrite string processing for subtree
 44962                                  ;				    aliasing.
 44963                                  ;
 44964                                  ;   MSDOS performs several types of name translation. First, we maintain for
 44965                                  ;   each valid drive letter the text of the current directory on that drive.
 44966                                  ;   For invalid drive letters, there is no current directory so we pretend to
 44967                                  ;   be at the root. A current directory is either the raw local directory
 44968                                  ;   (consisting of drive:\path) or a local network directory (consisting of
 44969                                  ;   \\machine\path. There is a limit on the point to which a .. is allowed.
 44970                                  ;
 44971                                  ;   Given a path, MSDOS will transform this into a real from-the-root path
 44972                                  ;   without . or .. entries. Any component that is > 8.3 is truncated to
 44973                                  ;   this and all * are expanded into ?'s.
 44974                                  ;
 44975                                  ;   The second part of name translation involves subtree aliasing. A list of
 44976                                  ;   subtree pairs is maintained by the external utility SUBST. The results of
 44977                                  ;   the previous 'canonicalization' are then examined to see if any of the
 44978                                  ;   subtree pairs is a prefix of the user path. If so, then this prefix is
 44979                                  ;   replaced with the other subtree in the pair.
 44980                                  ;
 44981                                  ;   A third part involves mapping this "real" path into a "physical" path.  A
 44982                                  ;   list of drive/subtree pairs are maintained by the external utility JOIN.
 44983                                  ;   The output of the previous translation is examined to see if any of the
 44984                                  ;   subtrees in this list are a prefix of the string. If so, then the prefix
 44985                                  ;   is replaced by the appropriate drive letter. In this manner, we can
 44986                                  ;   'mount' one device under another.
 44987                                  ;
 44988                                  ;   The final form of name translation involves the mapping of a user's
 44989                                  ;   logical drive number into the internal physical drive. This is
 44990                                  ;   accomplished by converting the drive number into letter:CON, performing
 44991                                  ;   the above translation and then converting the character back into a drive
 44992                                  ;   number.
 44993                                  ;
 44994                                  ;   There are two main entry points: TransPath and TransFCB. TransPath will
 44995                                  ;   take a path and form the real text of the pathname with all . and ..
 44996                                  ;   removed. TransFCB will translate an FCB into a path and then invoke
 44997                                  ;   TransPath.
 44998                                  ;
 44999                                  ;	A000	version 4.00  Jan. 1988
