 48461                                  ;
 48462                                  ; procedure : Rational386Patch
 48463                                  ;
 48464                                  ; Older versions of the Rational DOS Extender have several bugs which trash
 48465                                  ; 386 registers (usually just the high word of 32 bit registers) during
 48466                                  ; interrupt processing. Lotus 123 3.1+ is a popular application that uses a
 48467                                  ; version of the Rational extender with the 32 bit register trashing bugs.
 48468                                  ;
 48469                                  ; This routine applies patches to the Rational DOS Extender to work around
 48470                                  ; most of the register trashing bugs.
 48471                                  ;
 48472                                  ; Note that there are additional register trashing bugs not fixed by these
 48473                                  ; patches. In particular, the high word of ESP and the FS and GS registers
 48474                                  ; may be modified on interrupts.
 48475                                  ;
 48476                                  ; There are two different Rational DOS Extender patchs in this module.
 48477                                  ; Rational386Patch is to correct 386 register trashing bugs on 386 or later
 48478                                  ; processors. This patch code is executed when MS-DOS is running on a 386
 48479                                  ; or later processor, regardless of whether MS-DOS is running in the HMA
 48480                                  ; or not.
 48481                                  ;
 48482                                  ; The other Rational patch routine (RationalPatch, below) fixes a register
 48483                                  ; trashing problem on 286 processors, and is only executed if MS-DOS is
 48484                                  ; running in the HMA.
 48485                                  ;
 48486                                  ; This patch detection and replacement is based on an example supplied by
 48487                                  ; Ben Williams at Rational.
 48488                                  ;
 48489                                  ;----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 48490                                  
 48491                                  ; 22/05/2019 - Retro DOS v4.0
 48492                                  ; DOSCODE:B448h (MSDOS 6.21, MSDOS.SYS)
 48493                                  
 48494                                  ;----------------------------------------------------------------------------
