 53357                                  ; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 53358                                  ;
 53359                                  ; The following table defines CLASS ACTION and LOCUS info for the INT 21H
 53360                                  ; errors. Each entry is 4 bytes long:
 53361                                  ;
 53362                                  ;       Err#,Class,Action,Locus
 53363                                  ;
 53364                                  ; A value of 0FFh indicates a call specific value (ie. should already
 53365                                  ; be set). AN ERROR CODE NOT IN THE TABLE FALLS THROUGH TO THE CATCH ALL AT
 53366                                  ; THE END, IT IS ASSUMES THAT CLASS, ACTION, LOCUS IS ALREADY SET.
 53367                                  ;
 53368                                  ; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 53369                                  
 53370                                  ;ErrTab  Macro   err,class,action,locus
 53371                                  ;ifidn <locus>,<0FFh>
 53372                                  ;    DB  error_&err,errCLASS_&class,errACT_&action,0FFh
 53373                                  ;ELSE
 53374                                  ;    DB  error_&err,errCLASS_&class,errACT_&action,errLOC_&locus
 53375                                  ;ENDIF
 53376                                  ;ENDM
